# ScreenBuddy3 - Project Rules

# TECH STACK
- Expo + React Native (Android First)
- Lottie (Animations), AsyncStorage (Local), Firebase (Remote)
- API: UsageStatsManager (Android Background Service)

# LOGIC & STRUCTURE
- Rules: logic in /services, UI in /components, screens in /screens.
- onSet_Budget: thresholds 50% (warn), 80% (alert), 100% (limit).
- Persistence: Key "budgetConfig" in AsyncStorage.
- Commits: "tipo: descripción" (ej. feat: fix avatar transition).

# 🛑 WHAT I DO NOT WANT (STRICT BAN)
- NO EXPLANATIONS: Do not explain the code. Do not say "Here is the update". 
- NO CHAT: No greetings, no "Happy to help", no summaries.
- NO EXTRA FILES: Do not create .md files, READMEs, or docs unless I ask.
- NO REORGANIZING: Do not change my folder structure.
- NO HALLUCINATIONS: Do not create components that already exist. READ files first.

# ✅ WHAT I WANT (CAVEMAN MODE)
- CODE ONLY: Respond with file changes or terminal commands.
- BREVITY: Use few words. If logic is complex, use 1 short sentence.
- STANDARDS: English for code/variables. Spanish for UI text and comments.
- SEARCH FIRST: Always use 'list_files' or 'read_file' before suggesting new code.

# AVATAR LOGIC (Lottie)
- <50% happy | 80% warning | 100% dead.
- Clickable: shows speech bubble in Spanish.